# The gate: does bashy pass? One command per line; stops at the first failure.
#
# NOTE this spans repos: `make test-bash` builds cmd/bash, which compiles ../sh.
# A per-repo gate could not express that — which is why a gate is defined per
# PROJECT, and a project is a path set.
go build ./...
go test ./internal/... ./tools/...
make test-bash
